snippet: VNSNY Choice, part of the Visiting Nurse Service of New York, admitted that it had enrolled ineligible members, including some referred by social adult day care centers.
abstract: VNSNY Choice, part of Visiting Nurse Service of New York and the largest managed long-term care agency in New York, agrees to repay $33.6 million to state's Medicaid program; agency has admitted to improper billings linked to use of social adult day care centers by enrolling ineligible members.
lead_paragraph: VNSNY Choice, part of the Visiting Nurse Service of New York, admitted that it had enrolled ineligible members, including some referred by social adult day care centers.

headline.main: Long-Term Care Agency to Repay Millions to Medicaid for Enrolling Ineligible Patients
headline.print_headline: Long-Term Care Agency to Repay Millions to Medicaid for Enrolling Ineligible Patients
